Invacare Corp chairman, presidentand chief executive officer A. Malachi Mixon III said heexpects the home healthcare equipment company to post salesincreases in the 10 to 15 pct range in 1987.    Mixon said the increases should come from internal growthas well as potential acquisitions.    "Invacare is aggressively seeking acquisitions tocomplement the company's existing product lines," Mixon said.    Earlier, the company reported fourth quarter 1986 net of1.5 mln dlrs, or 26 cts a share, up from 1.1 mln dlrs, or 19cts a share, in 1985's fourth quarter.    Invacare also reported 1986 net income of 3.4 mln dlrs, or60 cts a share, up from a loss of 1.1 mln dlrs, or 19 cts ashare, in 1985. Reuter&#3;